   "source": [
    "## Model Debugging Report\n",
    "\n",
    "| Bug | Description | Why It's Dangerous | Fix |\n",
    "|-----|------------|-------------------|-----|\n",
    "| **Bug 1 — No Train/Test Split** | Model trained and evaluated on the SAME data | Like memorizing exam answers. Gives 95%+ accuracy but fails on new data | Use `train_test_split()` to separate training and testing data |\n",
    "| **Bug 2 — Data Leakage (Scaler Before Split)** | StandardScaler fit on ALL data before split | Model learns test data distribution → unrealistic performance | Fit scaler only on training data, then transform test data |\n",
    "| **Bug 3 — Target in Features** | Churn column included in X | Model uses answer to predict answer → fake 100% accuracy | Remove target column from features |\n",
    "| **Bug 4 — Evaluating on Training Data** | Using `accuracy_score(y, model.predict(X))` | Measures memorization, not generalization | Always evaluate on `X_test` and `y_test` |\n",
    "| **Bug 5 — Categoricals Not Encoded** | String values passed directly to model | Model may crash or ignore features | Encode using OneHotEncoder / LabelEncoder |\n",
    "| **Bug 6 — TotalCharges Not Converted** | Stored as string (object type) | Causes errors or NaN during training | Convert to numeric using `pd.to_numeric()` |\n",
    "| **Bug 7 — Imputation Using Full Data** | Missing values filled using full dataset stats | Data leakage from test set | Compute mean/median on training set only |\n",
    "| **Bug 8 — Class Imbalance Ignored** | 26.5% churn vs 73.5% non-churn | Model predicts majority class → misleading accuracy | Use SMOTE or `class_weight='balanced'` |\n",
    "| **Bug 9 — No random_state** | Model initialized without random_state | Results change every run → not reproducible | Set `random_state=42` |\n",
    "| **Bug 10 — Model Not Saved** | Model not persisted after training | Cannot reuse or deploy | Save using `joblib.dump()` |"
   ]
  },
  {
